Re: Japanese sentences in the Informal Present Negative.
by astaroth » Mon 08.31.2009 8:36 am Minarai wrote:When you want to say something like " I don't like" you can use also the expression "kirai da/desu". Though as far as I understand, kirai comes out rather stronger than "I don't like". It's more like "I hate" or "I detest". (In italiano potrebbe essere qualcosa del tipo "mi fa schifo" che come sai è abbastanza forte ...)
